The best approach for `File.*` and `Directory.*` is to adopt the **`System.IO.Abstractions`** NuGet package rather than writing custom wrappers. It's battle-tested, complete, and has built-in test helpers.

### 1. Install packages

```bash
dotnet add <YourProject> package System.IO.Abstractions
dotnet add <YourTestProject> package System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers
```

### 2. Register in DI

```csharp
// In Program.cs / Startup.cs:
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IFileSystem, FileSystem>();
```

### 3. Inject `IFileSystem` into your classes

**Before:**
```csharp
public class ConfigManager
{
    public string Load(string path) => File.ReadAllText(path);
    public void Save(string path, string data) => File.WriteAllText(path, data);
    public bool FolderExists(string path) => Directory.Exists(path);
}
```

**After:**
```csharp
public class ConfigManager(IFileSystem fileSystem)
{
    public string Load(string path)
        => fileSystem.File.ReadAllText(path);

    public void Save(string path, string data)
        => fileSystem.File.WriteAllText(path, data);

    public bool FolderExists(string path)
        => fileSystem.Directory.Exists(path);
}
```

### 4. Test with `MockFileSystem`

```csharp
var mockFs = new MockFileSystem(new Dictionary<string, MockFileData>
{
    { "/config.json", new MockFileData("{\"key\": \"value\"}") }
});

var manager = new ConfigManager(mockFs);

// Test reading
Assert.Equal("{\"key\": \"value\"}", manager.Load("/config.json"));

// Test writing
manager.Save("/output.txt", "hello");
Assert.Equal("hello", mockFs.File.ReadAllText("/output.txt"));

// Test directory check
Assert.False(manager.FolderExists("/nonexistent"));
```

### Key points

- **Only wrap what you use** — `IFileSystem` exposes `.File`, `.Directory`, `.Path`, etc., so it covers all three of your statics through one injection.
- Register as **singleton** — `FileSystem` is stateless.
- `MockFileSystem` gives you an in-memory filesystem; no temp files or cleanup needed in tests.

Once the package is installed and DI is wired up, you can use the `migrate-static-to-wrapper` skill to bulk-replace all call sites mechanically. Want me to do that?
